# The Problem Solving Process in Web Development


<div style="background-color: #F7F8FA; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px;"> <p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;">The Problem Solving Process is a tool for structured problem solving that is woven throughout the entire course to promote student growth and development. The Web Development unit introduces the Problem Solving Process in Lesson 1 with the <strong> Problem Solving Process with Design</strong>. Thereafter, the <strong>Problem Solving Process with Programming</strong> is introduced in the Lesson 5 mini-project and used for the remainder of the unit.
</p></div>
<br>

#### Below, you will find more information about the Problem Solving Process with Design and Programming. You **do not** need to study these carefully before progressing, nor do your students need to complete each bullet point within Define, Prepare, Try, and Reflect. Just take a moment to review each section, as you'll be introducing the following as a guiding framework to your students in Unit 2: Web Development.

